{"version":3,"character":{"id":145223,"userID":34493,"buildID":null,"name":"Friar Mungo","level":1,"experience":0,"currentHealth":null,"tempHealth":null,"heroPoints":1,"ancestryID":176,"heritageID":712,"uniHeritageID":null,"backgroundID":37,"classID":325,"classID_2":null,"inventoryID":145575,"notes":null,"infoJSON":"{\"imageURL\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Workshop_of_Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Portrait_of_a_Dominican_Friar.jpg\",\"appearance\":\"Stout\",\"personality\":\"Surly\",\"alignment\":\"\",\"age\":\"30\",\"gender\":\"Male\",\"pronouns\":\"\"}","rollHistoryJSON":null,"details":"","customCode":null,"dataID":null,"currentStamina":null,"currentResolve":null,"builderByLevel":0,"optionAutoDetectPreReqs":1,"optionAutoHeightenSpells":0,"optionPublicCharacter":0,"optionCustomCodeBlock":0,"optionDiceRoller":0,"optionClassArchetypes":1,"optionIgnoreBulk":0,"variantProfWithoutLevel":0,"variantFreeArchetype":0,"variantAncestryParagon":0,"variantStamina":0,"variantAutoBonusProgression":0,"variantGradualAbilityBoosts":0,"enabledSources":"[\"CRB\",\"ADV-PLAYER-GUIDE\",\"GM-GUIDE\",\"BEST-1\",\"BEST-2\",\"BEST-3\",\"CLASS-ARCHETYPES-OPTION\",\"LOST-CITY-ABSALOM\",\"LOST-ANCESTRY-GUIDE\"]","enabledHomebrew":"[null]","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:15:49.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:06:47.000Z","_class":{"id":325,"name":"Cleric","rarity":"COMMON","description":"__Deities work their will upon the world in infinite ways, and you serve as one of their most stalwart mortal servants. Blessed with divine magic, you live the ideals of your faith, adorn yourself with the symbols of your church, and train diligently to wield your deity’s favored weapon. Your spells might protect and heal your allies, or they might punish foes and enemies of your faith, as your deity wills. Yours is a life of devotion, spreading the teachings of your faith through both word and deed.__\n----\n***During Combat Encounters...***\nIf you’re a warpriest, you balance between casting spells and attacking with weapons— typically the favored weapon of your deity. If you’re a cloistered cleric, you primarily cast spells. Most of your spells can boost, protect, or heal your allies. Depending on your deity, you get extra spells to heal your allies or harm your enemies.\n***During Social Encounters...***\nYou might make diplomatic overtures or deliver impressive speeches. Because you’re wise, you also pick up on falsehoods others tell.\n***While Exploring...***\nYou detect nearby magic and interpret any religious writing you come across. You might also concentrate on a protective spell for your allies in case of attack. After a battle or hazard, you might heal anyone who was hurt.\n***In Downtime...***\nYou might perform services at a temple, travel to spread the word of your deity, research scripture, celebrate holy days, or even found a new temple.\n***You Might...***\n* : Visit the temples and holy places sacred to your faith, and have an immediate affinity with other worshippers of your deity.\n* : Know the teachings of your religion’s holy texts and how they apply to a dilemma.\n* : Cooperate with your allies, provided they don’t ask you to go against divine will.\n***Others Probably...***\n* : Find your devotion impressive, even if they don’t understand it.\n* : Expect you to heal their wounds.\n* : Rely on you to interact with other religious figures.","keyAbility":"Wisdom","hitPoints":8,"tPerception":"T","tFortitude":"T","tReflex":"T","tWill":"E","tClassDC":"U","tSkills":"Religion","tSkillsMore":2,"tWeapons":"T:::Unarmed Attacks,,, T:::Simple Weapons","weaponsExtra":null,"tArmor":"T:::Unarmored Defense","tagID":841,"artworkURL":"/images/community_use/Cleric - Kyra.png","code":null,"isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"version":"1.1","createdAt":"2020-08-24T08:46:40.000Z","updatedAt":"2020-08-24T08:46:40.000Z"},"_background":{"id":37,"name":"Herbalist","rarity":"COMMON","description":"__As a formally trained apothecary or a rural practitioner of folk medicine, you learned the healing properties of various herbs. You’re adept at collecting the right natural cures in all sorts of environments and preparing them properly.__\nChoose two ability boosts. One must be to Constitution or Wisdom, and one is a free ability boost.\nYou’re trained in the Nature skill and the Herbalism Lore skill. You gain the (feat: Natural Medicine) skill feat.","boostOne":"CON,WIS","boostTwo":"ALL","code":"GIVE-PROF-IN=Nature:T\nGIVE-LORE=Herbalism\nGIVE-FEAT-NAME=Natural Medicine","isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"version":"1.0"},"_ancestry":{"id":176,"name":"Human","rarity":"COMMON","hitPoints":8,"size":"MEDIUM","speed":25,"description":"__As unpredictable and varied as any of Golarion’s peoples, humans have exceptional drive and the capacity to endure and expand. Though many civilizations thrived before humanity rose to prominence, humans have built some of the greatest and the most terrible societies throughout the course of history, and today they are the most populous people in the realms around the Inner Sea.__\nHumans’ ambition, versatility, and exceptional potential have led to their status as the world’s predominant ancestry. Their empires and nations are vast, sprawling things, and their citizens carve names for themselves with the strength of their sword arms and the power of their spells. Humanity is diverse and tumultuous, running the gamut from nomadic to imperial, sinister to saintly. Many of them venture forth to explore, to map the expanse of the multiverse, to search for long-lost treasure, or to lead mighty armies to conquer their neighbors—for no better reason than because they can.\nIf you want a character who can be just about anything, you should play a human.\n***You Might...***\n* : Strive to achieve greatness, either in your own right or on behalf of a cause.\n* : Seek to understand your purpose in the world.\n* : Cherish your relationships with family and friends.\n***Others Probably...***\n* : Respect your flexibility, your adaptability, and—in most cases—your open-mindedness.\n* : Distrust your intentions, fearing you seek only power or wealth.\n* : Aren't sure what to expect from you and are hesitant to assume your intentions.\n***Physical Description***\nHumans' physical characteristics are as varied as the world's climes. Humans have a wide variety of skin and hair colors, body types, and facial features. Generally speaking, their skin has a darker hue the closer to the equator they or their ancestors lived. Humans reach physical adulthood around the age of 15, though mental maturity occurs a few years later. A typical human can live to be around 90 years old. Humans often intermarry with people of other ancestries, giving rise to children who bear the traits of both parents. The most notable half-humans are half-elves and half-orcs.\n***Society***\nHuman variety also manifests in terms of their governments, attitudes, and social norms. Though the oldest of human cultures can trace their shared histories thousands of years into the past, when compared to the societies of the elves or dwarves, human civilizations seem in a state of constant flux as empires fragment and new kingdoms subsume the old.\n***Alignment and Religion***\nHumanity is perhaps the most heterogeneous of all the ancestries, with a capacity for great evil and boundless good. Some humans assemble into vast raging hordes, while others build sprawling cities. Considered as a whole, most humans are neutral, yet they tend to congregate into nations or communities of a shared alignment, or at least a shared tendency toward an alignment. Humans also worship a wide range of gods and practice many different religions, tending to seek favor from any divine being they encounter.\n***Names***\nUnlike many ancestral cultures, which generally cleave to specific traditions and shared histories, humanity's diversity has resulted in a near-infinite set of names. The humans of northern tribes have different names than those dwelling in southern nation-states. Humans throughout much of the world speak Common (though some continents on Golarion have their own regional common languages), yet their names are as varied as their beliefs and appearances.","visionSenseID":1,"additionalSenseID":null,"physicalFeatureOneID":null,"physicalFeatureTwoID":null,"tagID":835,"artworkURL":"/images/community_use/Human - Kasmir.png","isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"version":"1.2"},"_heritage":{"id":712,"name":"Skilled Human","ancestryID":176,"rarity":"COMMON","description":"Your ingenuity allows you to train in a wide variety of skills. You become trained in one skill of your choice. At 5th level, you become an expert in the chosen skill.","code":"IF (HAS-LEVEL>=5) {GIVE-SKILL=E} ELSE {GIVE-SKILL=T}","isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","indivAncestryName":null,"homebrewID":null}},"charTraits":[{"charID":145223,"source":"charTag","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"defaultTag","sourceCodeSNum":"a","value":"Human","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:17:06.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:17:06.000Z"}],"build":{"boosts":[{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"boost-choose","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"WIS:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:26:00.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:26:00.000Z","Ability":"WIS","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"boost-choose","sourceCodeSNum":"ba","value":"CHA:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:26:13.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:26:13.000Z","Ability":"CHA","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"background","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"boost-choose","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"CON:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:19:23.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:19:23.000Z","Ability":"CON","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"background","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"boost-choose","sourceCodeSNum":"ba","value":"WIS:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:19:35.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:19:35.000Z","Ability":"WIS","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13620","sourceCodeSNum":"aaa","value":"CON:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:21:50.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:21:50.000Z","Ability":"CON","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13620","sourceCodeSNum":"baa","value":"WIS:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:21:53.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:21:53.000Z","Ability":"WIS","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13620","sourceCodeSNum":"caa","value":"CHA:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:22:16.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:22:16.000Z","Ability":"CHA","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13620","sourceCodeSNum":"daa","value":"DEX:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T02:22:07.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T02:22:07.000Z","Ability":"DEX","Bonus":"Boost"},{"charID":145223,"source":"abilityBonus","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"keyAbility","sourceCodeSNum":"a","value":"WIS:::Boost","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","Ability":"WIS","Bonus":"Boost"}],"domains":[{"charID":145223,"source":"domains","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbilitySelector-13622","sourceCodeSNum":"aaa","value":{"id":22,"name":"Healing","description":"**Domain Spell:** (spell: Healer's Blessing)\n**Advanced Domain Spell:** (spell: Rebuke Death)\n----\nYour healing magic is particularly potent.\n","initialSpellID":574,"advancedSpellID":575,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"createdAt":"2020-06-07T14:14:44.000Z","updatedAt":"2020-06-07T14:14:44.000Z"}}],"feats":[{"charID":145223,"source":"chosenFeats","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"ancestryFeat-0","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":{"id":10151,"name":"Natural Skill","actions":"NONE","level":1,"rarity":"COMMON","prerequisites":null,"frequency":null,"cost":null,"trigger":null,"requirements":null,"description":"Your ingenuity allows you to learn a wide variety of skills. You gain the trained proficiency rank in two skills of your choice.","special":null,"canSelectMultiple":0,"isDefault":0,"skillID":null,"minProf":null,"code":"GIVE-SKILL=T\nGIVE-SKILL=T","isCore":0,"genericType":null,"genTypeName":null,"isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"version":"1.0","createdAt":"2020-08-23T22:16:27.000Z","updatedAt":"2020-08-23T22:16:27.000Z"}},{"charID":145223,"source":"chosenFeats","sourceType":"background","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"background","sourceCodeSNum":"ca","value":{"id":2214,"name":"Natural Medicine","actions":"NONE","level":1,"rarity":"COMMON","prerequisites":"trained in Nature","frequency":null,"cost":null,"trigger":null,"requirements":null,"description":"You can apply natural cures to heal your allies. You can use Nature instead of Medicine to (Action: Treat Wounds). If you’re in the wilderness, you might have easier access to fresh ingredients, allowing you to gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your check to (Action: Treat Wounds) using Nature, subject to the GM’s determination.","special":null,"canSelectMultiple":0,"isDefault":0,"skillID":11,"minProf":null,"code":null,"isCore":0,"genericType":"SKILL-FEAT","genTypeName":null,"isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"version":"1.0","createdAt":"2020-06-20T22:17:35.000Z","updatedAt":"2020-06-20T22:17:35.000Z"}},{"charID":145223,"source":"chosenFeats","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbilitySelector-13622","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":{"id":10293,"name":"Domain Initiate","actions":"NONE","level":1,"rarity":"COMMON","prerequisites":null,"frequency":null,"cost":null,"trigger":null,"requirements":null,"description":"Your deity bestows a special spell related to their powers. Select one domain – a subject of particular interest to you within your religion – from your deity’s list. You gain an initial domain spell for that domain, a spell unique to the domain and not available to other clerics.\nDomain spells are a type of focus spell. It costs 1 Focus Point to cast a focus spell, and you start with a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the (action: Refocus) activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes.\nFocus spells are automatically heightened to half your level rounded up. Focus spells don’t require spell slots, nor can you cast them using spell slots. Certain feats can give you more focus spells and increase the size of your focus pool, though your focus pool can never hold more than 3 Focus Points. The full rules for focus spells appear on page 300.","special":"You can select this feat multiple times, selecting a different domain each time and gaining its domain spell.","canSelectMultiple":1,"isDefault":0,"skillID":null,"minProf":null,"code":"GIVE-DOMAIN=Cleric\nGIVE-FOCUS-POINT","isCore":0,"genericType":null,"genTypeName":null,"isArchived":0,"contentSrc":"CRB","homebrewID":null,"version":"1.0","createdAt":"2020-08-24T08:46:40.000Z","updatedAt":"2020-08-24T08:46:40.000Z"}}],"languages":[{"charID":145223,"source":"languages","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-0","sourceCodeSNum":"a","value":{"id":1,"name":"Common","speakers":"Humans, Dwarves, Elves, Halflings, and other common ancestries","script":"Common","description":"Common is a relative term used to denote the most prevalent human language spoken in a particular region. In each different region there may be different dialects and variations in the common language. In general, Common is the name for the standard language in which most humanoids speak.","homebrewID":null,"createdAt":"2019-12-13T00:32:51.000Z","updatedAt":"2019-12-13T00:32:51.000Z"}},{"charID":145223,"source":"languages","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-bonus-lang","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":{"id":10,"name":"Sylvan","speakers":"Fey, Centaurs, plant creatures","script":"Rellanic","description":"The language of the fey, Sylvan is one of the most linguistically static of all languages. Thought to be nearly as old as (language: Draconic) or (language: Abyssal), Sylvan has a tiny vocabulary, which has barely changed over the eons.","homebrewID":null,"createdAt":"2019-12-13T00:36:05.000Z","updatedAt":"2019-12-13T00:36:05.000Z"}}],"proficiencies":[{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"ancestryFeat-0","sourceCodeSNum":"aaa","value":"Skill:::Intimidation:::T:::Natural Skill (Lvl 1)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"Intimidation","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Natural Skill (Lvl 1)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"ancestryFeat-0","sourceCodeSNum":"baa","value":"Skill:::Stealth:::T:::Natural Skill (Lvl 1)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"Stealth","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Natural Skill (Lvl 1)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"ancestry","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"heritage","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Skill:::Medicine:::T:::Heritage","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"Medicine","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Heritage"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"background","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"background","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Skill:::Nature:::T:::Background","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"Nature","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Background"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"background","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"background","sourceCodeSNum":"ba","value":"Skill:::HERBALISM_LORE:::T:::Background","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"HERBALISM_LORE","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Background"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13623","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"SpellAttack:::DivineSpellAttacks:::T:::Divine Spellcasting (Lvl 1)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"SpellAttack","To":"DivineSpellAttacks","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Divine Spellcasting (Lvl 1)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13623","sourceCodeSNum":"ba","value":"SpellDC:::DivineSpellDCs:::T:::Divine Spellcasting (Lvl 1)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"SpellDC","To":"DivineSpellDCs","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Divine Spellcasting (Lvl 1)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"classAbility-13624","sourceCodeSNum":"ba","value":"Skill:::Survival:::T:::Deity (Lvl 1)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"Survival","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Deity (Lvl 1)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-0","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Perception:::Perception:::T:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","For":"Perception","To":"Perception","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-1","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Skill:::Religion:::T:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:09.000Z","For":"Skill","To":"Religion","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-2","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Save:::Fortitude:::T:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Save","To":"Fortitude","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-3","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Save:::Reflex:::T:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Save","To":"Reflex","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-4","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Save:::Will:::E:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Save","To":"Will","Prof":"E","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-5","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Attack:::Unarmed_Attacks:::T:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Attack","To":"Unarmed_Attacks","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","sourceLevel":1,"sourceCode":"inits-6","sourceCodeSNum":"aa","value":"Attack:::Simple_Weapons:::T:::Initial Prof (Class)","createdAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-19T03:07:10.000Z","For":"Attack","To":"Simple_Weapons","Prof":"T","SourceName":"Initial Prof (Class)"},{"charID":145223,"source":"proficiencies","sourceType":"class","